Eggdrop
=======

The world's most popular IRC bot, running since 1993. Modular,
scriptable, with native I/O backends for every major platform.

This is a personal fork by devinkbrown. Upstream: https://github.com/eggheads/eggdrop


Why this fork exists
--------------------

Upstream Eggdrop is an excellent IRC bot with 30+ years of proven
functionality, but it carries significant technical debt from its long
history:

1. The build system was autoconf/make — fragile, slow, and difficult
   to extend. This fork replaces it with Meson + Ninja, which is
   faster, easier to maintain, and works out of the box on Linux,
   macOS, Windows (MinGW and MSVC), and Cygwin.

2. Native Windows support never existed in upstream. Eggdrop's net.c
   was written for POSIX and had no path for Windows async I/O. This
   fork adds a proper IOCP (I/O Completion Ports) backend so Eggdrop
   runs as a first-class Windows process without Cygwin emulation.

3. Tcl was a hard dependency — you could not build or run the bot
   without it. This fork makes Tcl fully optional. Python can serve
   as the sole scripting engine, and the bot is functional even with
   no scripting at all.

4. The configuration format was a Tcl script that required chmod u+x
   and Tcl knowledge to edit. This fork adds TOML as the primary
   config format (clean key=value syntax, no programming knowledge
   needed) plus an interactive setup wizard.

5. The codebase used unsafe C patterns accumulated over decades — raw
   strcpy, sprintf, atoi, unbounded sscanf, and a weak PRNG seeded
   with pid+time. This fork systematically eliminates all of them.

6. There was no test suite. This fork adds comprehensive tests that
   run under address and undefined-behaviour sanitisers.


Why libop
---------

Writing an IOCP backend from scratch inside a foreign codebase is
error-prone. The hard parts are: getting the OVERLAPPED structure
layout right, handling stale completions after socket close, draining
the completion port safely, and avoiding double-frees.

libop is the I/O layer of the ophion IRC server
(https://github.com/devinkbrown/ophion), written by the same author.
It had already solved all of these problems in production-tested C:

  - Zero-byte overlapped WSARecv/WSASend arms readiness notifications
    without touching the data buffer, matching how epoll/kqueue work.
  - The OVERLAPPED struct is the first member of every pending
    operation, so GetQueuedCompletionStatus casts back without UB.
  - Stale completions are detected by recording socket fd + slot
    index at arm time and checking on arrival.
  - Read/write arms are tracked per-slot to prevent double-arming.

Adapting libop meant the Windows backend could be dropped in as a
single reviewed unit rather than bolted on incrementally. Beyond
IOCP, libop also provides the dynamic string builder (op_strbuf_t),
slab allocator (op_bh), hash tables (op_htab), line buffer
(op_linebuf), and LMDB — all used throughout this fork.


What changed
------------

Build & platform:
  - Meson + Ninja replaces autoconf/make
  - Native Windows support via IOCP (MinGW and MSVC)
  - Five I/O backends: io_uring, epoll, kqueue, IOCP, select
  - LTO, -fvisibility=hidden, -fno-strict-aliasing by default
  - C23 (gnu23) with -Wshadow=local enforced

Configuration:
  - TOML as primary config format (eggdrop.toml)
  - Interactive setup wizard: eggdrop --setup
  - Full parity with eggdrop.conf (128+ settings)
  - Per-channel settings via [[chanset]] blocks
  - Inline Tcl via [tcl] code = """..."""
  - Auto-create userfile on first run (no -m needed)

Scripting:
  - Tcl is fully optional (-Dtcl=disabled)
  - Python API at 100% parity with Tcl (239 commands)
  - Decorator-based binds, type annotations, dataclasses
  - scripts/eggtools.py as modern replacement for alltools.tcl

Storage:
  - Pluggable backend system (egg_store)
  - LMDB backend: crash-safe, auto-recovery, per-user sub-databases
  - Flat-file backend preserved for compatibility

Networking:
  - Bundled opssl TLS library (no external OpenSSL needed)
  - Async DNS resolver replacing threaded pthreads DNS
  - DNS-over-TLS (DoT, RFC 7858) support
  - op_linebuf for zero-memmove line framing
  - io_uring SQPOLL bug fixes

IRC protocol:
  - IRCX/Ophion protocol support (CREATE, PROP, ACCESS, +q owner)
  - Full IRCv3 capability set

Performance:
  - O(1) hash tables for channel members, bans, bind dispatch
  - Slab allocator for memberlist and masklist nodes
  - All allocation routed through libop (750+ sites)
  - Atomic traffic counters, CIDR trie for ban matching

Security:
  - CSPRNG: getrandom(2) / arc4random_buf replaces random()/srandom()
  - egg_atoi(): safe strtol wrapper replacing 202 raw atoi() calls
  - Zero remaining: strcpy, sprintf, strcat, strncpy, strncat, strtok,
    gets, system(), raw atoi, unbounded sscanf %s
  - strlcpy/strlcat → op_strbuf_t migration (127 sites)
  - SASL: PLAIN, EXTERNAL, SCRAM-SHA-256/512, ECDSA, ECDH-X25519

Code quality:
  - C23 modernisation: constexpr, bool, variable-at-first-use
  - Zero compiler warnings on GCC 15
  - Comprehensive test suite (7 executables, ASAN+UBSAN clean)
  - Pre-1.3.0 botnet dead code stripped

Legacy .conf files still work unchanged.


Quick start
-----------

    meson setup build/
    ninja -C build/
    ./eggdrop --setup mybot.toml
    ./eggdrop -m mybot.toml

See INSTALL for dependencies and platform-specific instructions.


I/O backends
------------

    Platform             Backend
    -------------------- ----------
    Linux >= 5.1         io_uring
    Linux                epoll
    macOS / BSD          kqueue
    Windows native       IOCP
    Cygwin / fallback    select()


Configuration
-------------

Minimal TOML config:

    [bot]
    nick  = "MyBot"
    owner = "MyNick"

    [servers]
    list = ["irc.libera.chat:+6697"]

    [channels]
    list = ["#mychannel"]

    [modules]
    load = ["pbkdf2", "blowfish", "channels", "server", "ctcp",
            "irc", "notes", "console", "uptime"]

Run eggdrop --setup for guided configuration, or see eggdrop.toml
for the full reference.


Python scripting
----------------

    import eggtools

    @eggtools.on_pub("!hello", "*")
    def greet(nick, host, handle, channel, text):
        eggtools.privmsg(channel, f"Hello, {nick}!")

Build without Tcl: meson setup build/ -Dtcl=disabled

The Python API covers all 239 commands: channel management, user
database, botnet, DCC, timers, and every IRC operation. See
scripts/eggtools.py for the complete API with docstrings.


Auto-restart
------------

    ./scripts/autobotchk mybot.toml -systemd   # systemd
    ./scripts/autobotchk mybot.toml             # crontab


